It has been an honor and a pleasure to have served alongside Congressman Loebsack and I look forward to working with him throughout the rest of his term to improve the lives of all Iowans.

Whether he was fighting to lift Iowans out of poverty, supporting our rural communities, or ensuring every Iowan had access to quality, affordable health care, Congressman Loebsack’s commitment to public service has been an inspiration to many, including myself.
.@daveloebsack has been a true champion for all Iowans during his seven terms in office.

Thank you to Secretary Perdue and the USDA for listening to the concerns of Iowans. I’m grateful this program has been authorized, but Iowa farmers need additional USDA programs in order to fully recover and rebuild. https://axne.house.gov/media/press-releases/following-rep-axne-request-usda-authorizes-emergency-relief-program-iowa …

I promised Iowans I would hold Washington accountable. When I found out the USDA had authorized programs to help Nebraska farmers but not Iowa, I wanted answers. I called on the USDA to immediately authorize programs to assist Iowa farmers impacted by the historic flood.

Today, I voted to restore net neutrality protections and make the Internet better, cheaper and faster for Iowa consumers, entrepreneurs & small biz. Restoring net neutrality will help create good-paying jobs and ensure that Iowa entrepreneurs can compete. https://axne.house.gov/media/press-releases/rep-axne-votes-restore-net-neutrality …

I'm very disappointed the Senate failed to pass a disaster funding bill. We can't turn our backs on our communities when they're recovering from the devastating damage of natural disasters. That’s not who we are as Iowans, and that’s not who we are as Americans.

I have never been more proud to call myself an Iowan than after seeing how our communities have come together to help one another recover from this devastating flood.
